        <h2 class="about-h">
          A community of faith<br>in the heart of <em>West Koratty</em>
        </h2>
        <p class="about-p">
          <strong>Fathima Matha Church</strong> — stands as a beacon of faith for our vibrant Syro-Malabar Catholic community.
          Established in <strong>1960</strong> under the Ernakulam–Angamaly Archeparchy,
          our parish welcomes over 1,800 faithful from around 431 families in the
          Padinjare Koratty and Mambra areas.
        </p>
        <div class="heritage-divider">
          <span></span>
          <span class="heritage-label">Our Spiritual Heritage</span>
          <span></span>
        </div>
        <p class="about-p">
          Dedicated to <strong>Our Lady of Fatima</strong>, our patroness whose apparitions
          in Portugal inspire devotion worldwide, the church reflects Koratty's deep Marian
          tradition. Nearby, the historic St. Mary's Church (Koratty Muthy) from the 14th
          century enriches our local Christian roots.
        </p>
        <p class="about-p">
          Our church is more than a place of worship — it is a <strong>family hub</strong>.
          Active groups include catechism classes for children, youth ministry, choir, and
          charitable outreach. From vibrant feasts to family retreats, we build bonds in
          faith, service, and joy, always under Fathima Matha's protective gaze.
        </p>

